alex.mojaki.boxes.observers.change

Class TargetedChangeObserver<T,V>

  • java.lang.Object
    • alex.mojaki.boxes.observers.change.TargetedChangeObserver<T,V>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type parameter of the PowerBoxes
    V - the type of the targets
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    ChangeObserver<T>

    public abstract class TargetedChangeObserver<T,V>
extends Object
implements ChangeObserver<T>
    A ChangeObserver which can associate specific objects with boxes, to overcome the fact that boxes share observers in a family rather than each storing their own. The onChange(PowerBox, Object, Object, Object, Object) method receives an additional parameter target which it can use to take a more specific action. Use the register(PowerBox, Object) method to create an association.

      • onChange

        public void onChange(PowerBox<T> box,
                     T originalValue,
                     T finalValue,
                     T requestedValue)
        Description copied from interface: ChangeObserver
        Take some action based on the values involved in the change. Called when the value of a PowerBox changes for zero or more of these objects.
        Specified by:
        onChange in interface ChangeObserver<T>
        Parameters:
        box - the PowerBox whose value changed.
        originalValue - the value the box contained before the change.
        finalValue - the new value the box will have. In the case of PowerBox.set(Object), this is the final result of applying all ChangeMiddleware.
        requestedValue - the parameter of PowerBox.set(Object), or just the same as originalValue in the case of a mutation to a WrapperBox.

      • register

        public void register(PowerBox<T> box,
                     V target)
        Create an association between box and target, and add this observer to box. When box changes, this observer's special onChange(PowerBox, Object, Object, Object, Object) method will be called with target as the last argument.

      • onChange

        public abstract void onChange(PowerBox<T> box,
                              T originalValue,
                              T finalValue,
                              T requestedValue,
                              V target)
        Similar to the normal ChangeObserver.onChange(PowerBox, Object, Object, Object) method, except that when box changes, this method is called once for every value of target that was associated with box via the register(PowerBox, Object) method.
